title: Tigers oust Hawks from 1A regional
text:
Tigers oust Hawks from 1A regional Published: Wednesday, Oct. 21, 2015 11:08 a.m. CDT • Updated: Wednesday, Oct. 21, 2015 12:06 p.m. CDT Caption (Jocelyn Sheets/Daily News) Making a save in a home match earlier in the season is Lynnville-Sully senior Brenna Lanser (21). Lanser led the Hawks in digs, kills and ace serves this season. The Hawks’ season ended Monday in a first-round Class 1A regional loss at ninth-ranked Iowa Valley in Marengo. By Jocelyn Sheets Newton Daily News 
MARENGO — A week ago Lynnville-Sully faced Iowa Valley in South Iowa Cedar League action. It lost in three sets. 
The two SICL teams were in the same place Tuesday with No. 9 Iowa Valley hosting Lynnville-Sully in Class1A Region 5 volleyball play. It was the same result as the Tigers halted the Hawks’ season with a 25-7, 25-12, 25-10 win in the postseason first round. 
Brenna Lanser put down eight kills and had eight digs in the match. Carson Fish was credited with six set assists while Skyler Young had four set assists and five digs. 
Kristen Van Der Wilt went 6-for-6 at the service line for the Hawks. She had nine digs. Shelby Foster was 4-for-4 at the service line and had three digs and one kill. 
“I was very happy how we placed in the conference,” Hawk head coach Heather James said. “We went severa matches to five sets and came out with a win. These players are very tough and can finish what they set out to accomplish.” 
Lynnville-Sully finished 10-9 overall. The Hawks went 7-4 in SICL play, finishing behind conference champion Iowa Valley (11-0) and Montezuma and North Mahaska, both at 9-2. 
In other Region 5 matches Monday, Montezuma beat Belle Plaine, 25-10, 25-12, 22-25, 24-26, 15-12; HLV defeated Ankeny Christian 20-25, 25-22, 25-17, 25-19; Colo-NESCO beat Meskwaki Settlement 8-25, 25-20, 21-25, 25-16, 15-11; North Tama beat GMB 25-16, 25-12, 21-25, 25-23; and Gladbrook-Reinbeck over AGWSR 23-25, 25-23, 25-14, 25-19. 
Colfax-Mingo, which earned a first-round bye, travels to Victor to play HLV in the second round. That match is Tuesday at 7 p.m.
